        "timestamp": "2021-07-01 14:27:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nIf all poms pointing to binding-parent -> do you think it will be good to just point sdnr/wt/pom.xml to binding-parent and maintain parent-child module hierarchy (example: sdnr/wt/pom.xml to binding-parent and have all child modules poms changed to have parent as:\n\n<groupId>org.onap.ccsdk.features.sdnr.wt</groupId>\n<artifactId>sdnr-wt</artifactId>",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "0b4b4db29211ac784536336eca65068e88373544",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 87,
          "name": "Dan Timoney",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dtimoney@att.com",
          "username": "djtimoney"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-07-01 20:46:40.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n> \n> If all poms pointing to binding-parent -> do you think it will be good to just point sdnr/wt/pom.xml to binding-parent and maintain parent-child module hierarchy (example: sdnr/wt/pom.xml to binding-parent and have all child modules poms changed to have parent as:\n> \n> <groupId>org.onap.ccsdk.features.sdnr.wt</groupId>\n> <artifactId>sdnr-wt</artifactId>\n\nThis is a good suggestion.  The only concern I'd have is that we'll need to make sure the mvn versions plugin still works ... I remember running into issues before with maven versions getting confused if there's a mix of parent-child and non-parent-child in the same multimodule project (which means sometimes not all the modules get built in the staging build - which uses versions plugin).  So, I would suggest maybe looking at that change in a separate code review, so that it doesn't hold up these fixes.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
